First Quantum Says Zambian Copper Belt Could Produce 1 Million Tons a Year

-- B y   N a t h a n   C r o o k s
-- 
2011-04-06T13:51:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/first-quantum-says-zambian-copper-belt-could-produce-1-million-tons-a-year.html
First Quantum Minerals Ltd. (FM)  said
total output from a new copper-producing region in Zambia may
reach 1 million metric tons a year by 2014. Company President
 Clive Newall  spoke today at a conference in Santiago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Crooks in Santiago at 
 ncrooks@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Attwood at 
 jattwood3@bloomberg.net  